author: Christian Berthelsen
title: Analysts Expect Increase in U.S. Oil Stockpiles
text:
U.S. crude-oil stocks are expected to rise in data due Wednesday from the Department of Energy, according to a survey of analysts by The Wall Street Journal.
Estimates from 10 analysts surveyed showed that U.S. oil inventories are projected to have increased by 300,000 barrels, on average, in the week ended September 25.
